Challenges:}
\par \pard\plain \s0\ql\nowidctlpar\ltrpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\cf1\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af13\afs24\alang1081\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\cf1\b\ab\rtlch \ltrch\loch\loch\f4

\par \pard\plain \s0\ql\nowidctlpar\ltrpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\cf1\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af13\afs24\alang1081\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0{\cf1\rtlch \ltrch\loch\loch\f4
\tab There will undoubtedly be challenges to achieving these goals.  First and foremost, The Kinect and Leap are imperfect sensors. This means our framework must be able to operate smoothly despite unexpected or incorrect data values from events. This challenge is compounded by the fact that children tend to be spontaneous, and their actions are not always predictable. Having children as the main users of the application also presents the challenge of hiding the hardware in the space so that it is protected from and not distracting to the children. The effectiveness of the framework would be undermined if kids were to start playing with (and potentially breaking) the sensors themselves rather than the space.  Another factor contributing to this obstacle is the fact that not all rooms are identical.  Our framework must be flexible enough to be able to handle spaces that vary widely.  Furthermore, not all kids are identical. Children all play differently and find interest in different things. The application must be effective for all kinds of sensory-seeking children. }{\cf1\rtlch \ltrch\loch\loch\f4
Determining the effectiveness of the framework requires consulting the knowledge of an expert in special education.}{\cf1\rtlch \ltrch\loch\loch\f4
 }{\cf1\rtlch \ltrch\loch\loch\f4
Also,}{\cf1\rtlch \ltrch\loch\loch\f4
 in order to reduce the amount of training needed to set up and operate the system, }{\cf1\rtlch \ltrch\loch\loch\f4
we will need to consult an expert in human-computer interaction to create}{\cf1\rtlch \ltrch\loch\loch\f4
 a user interface that }{\cf1\rtlch \ltrch\loch\loch\f4
is intuitive so as to be easily used by most. Lastly, determining and responding to one's mood using basic motion detection is an unsolved problem in computing sciences. }
